  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why does Quora Android app is not working?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why the Quora Android app might not be working. Here are some common issues and possible solutions:\n\n### 1. **App Crashes or Freezes**\n   - **Outdated App Version**: Ensure you have the latest version of the Quora app. Go to the Google Play Store, search for Quora, and update it if needed.\n   - **Corrupted Cache or Data**: Clear the app's cache and data. Go to **Settings > Apps > Quora > Storage > Clear Cache/Clear Data**.\n   - **Device Compatibility**: Your Android device or OS version might not be supported. Check the app's requirements on the Play Store.\n\n### 2. **Internet Connectivity Issues**\n   - **Weak or Unstable Connection**: Check your Wi-Fi or mobile data connection. Try switching between Wi-Fi and mobile data to see if it resolves the issue.\n   - **Network Restrictions**: Ensure your network isn't blocking Quora (e.g., in workplaces or schools).\n\n### 3. **Server-Side Issues**\n   - **Quora Server Problems**: The app might not be working due to server downtime or maintenance. Check Quora's social media accounts or forums for updates.\n   - **High Traffic**: During peak usage times, the app might experience slowdowns. Try again later.\n\n### 4. **App Not Opening**\n   - **Force Stop and Restart**: Go to **Settings > Apps > Quora > Force Stop**, then reopen the app.\n   - **Reinstall the App**: Uninstall Quora and reinstall it from the Google Play Store.\n\n### 5. **Permissions Issues**\n   - **Enable Necessary Permissions**: Go to **Settings > Apps > Quora > Permissions** and ensure all required permissions (e.g., storage, network) are enabled.\n\n### 6. **Device-Specific Issues**\n   - **Insufficient Storage**: Ensure your device has enough free storage to run the app.\n   - **Software Glitches**: Restart your device to resolve temporary glitches.\n   - **Conflicting Apps**: Some apps might interfere with Quora. Try running the app in safe mode to check for conflicts.\n\n### 7. **Account Issues**\n   - **Login Problems**: If the app is not logging you in, ensure your credentials are correct or reset your password.\n   - **Account Suspension**: Your account might be temporarily suspended. Check your email for notifications from Quora.\n\n### 8. **App Bugs**\n   - **Known Bugs**: Check if other users are experiencing similar issues on forums or Quora itself. Report the issue to Quora\u2019s support team.\n\n### What You Can Do:\n- **Check for Updates**: Ensure both the app and your Android OS are up to date.\n- **Contact Quora Support**: If the issue persists, reach out to Quora\u2019s support team via the app or their website.\n\nIf none of these solutions work, it\u2019s possible the issue is specific to your device or account, and further troubleshooting or professional assistance may be needed.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
